Package dr.math.interfaces

Interface Summary
ConjugateWishartStatisticsProvider An interface for classes that return conjugate outer products for Gibbs sampling of precision matrices
CurveMouseClickListener A CurveMouseClickListener defines an interface to handle mouse click performed on a scatterplot and passed to a curve definition.
ManyVariableFunction ManyVariableFunction is an interface for mathematical functions of many variables, that is functions of the form: f(X) where X is a vector.
OneVariableFunction OneVariableFunction is an interface for mathematical functions of a single variable, that is functions of the form f(x).
ParametrizedOneVariableFunction ParametrizedOneVariableFunction is an interface for mathematical functions of one variable depending on several parameters, that is functions of the form f(x;p), where p is a vector.
PointSeries PointSeries is an interface used by many classes of the package numericalMethods.
PointSeriesWithErrors This is a point series where each point has an error in the y direction.
